      "this rise and fall of walden at long intervals serves this use atleast the water standing at this great height for a year or morethough it makes it difficult to walk round it kills the shrubs andtrees which have sprung up about its edge since the last risepitch-pines birches alders aspens and others and falling againleaves an unobstructed shore for unlike many ponds and all waterswhich are subject to a daily tide its shore is cleanest when the wateris lowest\n",
